Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water
to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

Meanwhile, trim the @Brussels Sprouts{200}. Quarter them through the root, then pop
them onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread
out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until browned and tender, ~{15-18%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @Macaroni{180} and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{}
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @Onion{1}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in
another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring
occasionally, until golden, ~{8-10%mins}.

While the onion cooks, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{90%g}. Peel and grate the
@Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{25}, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g}
and @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set the cheesy crumb aside.

Once the onion is cooked, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%min} more.

Melt in the @Butter{20%g}, then stir in the @Plain Flour{1.5%tbsp}. Cook until it
forms a paste, ~{1-2%mins} - you've made a roux!

Stir in the @Water{250%ml} a little at a time, followed by the
@Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then stir and simmer until
thickened, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and @Dijon Mustard{10%g} into the sauce, then remove
from the heat. Stir through the Cheddar until melted, then season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, turn your grill on to high.

Once the Brussels sprouts and macaroni are cooked, gently stir them through the
cheese sauce. Add a splash of @?water{} if it needs loosening a little.

Transfer the mac & cheese to an appropriately-sized #ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle
over the cheesy crumb.

Once hot, grill until golden and bubbling, ~{3-4%mins}.

When ready, allow to stand for a couple of mins before sharing between your bowls.

Enjoy!